Sometimes after reading data, you need to clean or extract parts of a string.
String slicing:
word = "GermanShepherd"
print(word[0:6])   # German
print(word[-3:])   # rds (last 3 letters)

String functions:
text = "  hello world  "
print(text.strip())      # remove spaces â†’ "hello world"
print(text.upper())      # "HELLO WORLD"
print(text.replace("world", "Aishwarya"))  # "hello Aishwarya"

